---
import GuideLayout from '../layouts/GuideLayout.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'How much does n8n cost?',
    answer:
      'Self-hosted software has no license fee under fair-code terms. n8n Cloud pricing is per-workflow execution tiers — check n8n.io/pricing for current numbers.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Is n8n pricing cheaper than Zapier?',
    answer: 'Often yes at scale on self-host because you pay infrastructure, not per-task SaaS markup.',
  },
  {
    question: 'n8n price vs n8n pricing?',
    answer: 'Same topic — Cloud subscription tiers and optional enterprise support.',
  },
];
---

<GuideLayout
  title="n8n Pricing & Cost Guide (2025)"
  description="Understand n8n pricing, n8n price, and n8n Cloud tiers vs free self-host. Compare total cost with Zapier and Make."
  path="/n8n-pricing"
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', path: '/' },
    { name: 'n8n Pricing', path: '/n8n-pricing' },
  ]}
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <p>
    <strong>n8n pricing</strong> searches are steady worldwide (+20% recent week). Teams evaluate
    Cloud vs self-host before migrating from Zapier.
  </p>

  <h2>Self-hosted: software cost</h2>
  <p>
    The n8n application itself has no per-seat license when you self-host. Your bill is VPS + APIs
    (OpenAI, Apify, email tools). Templates on this site remain <a href="/free-n8n-workflows">free</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>n8n Cloud</h2>
  <p>
    Managed hosting charges by plan and execution volume. Good for agencies prototyping fast. See
    <a href="/n8n-cloud">n8n Cloud overview</a> and official pricing page for live numbers.
  </p>

  <h2>Hidden costs to plan for</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>LLM token usage on AI agent workflows</li>
    <li>Scraper actors (Apify) on lead-gen flows</li>
    <li>Engineer time maintaining Docker upgrades</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Comparisons</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/n8n-vs-zapier">n8n vs Zapier pricing logic</a></li>
    <li><a href="/n8n-vs-make">n8n vs Make</a></li>
  </ul>
</GuideLayout>
